        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
          Our mobile service includes no hidden fees — the price covers travel, equipment, water, and all <a href="https://www.chemicalguys.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-[#0f2a4a] font-semibold hover:text-[#c0c7cf]">Chemical Guys</a> products. We provide exact quotes before starting so you know the cost upfront. Call 754-215-2272 for a quick estimate based on your vehicle.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- How Often -->
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#0f2a4a] mb-4">How Often Should You Clean Car Upholstery in Florida?</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
          <strong>In Florida's humid climate, car upholstery should be professionally cleaned every 3-4 months to prevent mildew, bacteria growth, and permanent staining. Vehicles with pets, children, or daily commuters may need cleaning every 2-3 months. Regular upholstery cleaning also preserves resale value by preventing fabric and leather deterioration.</strong>
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
          South Florida's combination of heat, humidity, and salt air accelerates upholstery wear faster than northern climates. Moisture trapped in seat fabric breeds mold and bacteria within days. Sand tracked in from the beach acts as an abrasive, grinding down fibers every time you sit down. A regular cleaning schedule stops this cycle before permanent damage sets in.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Stain Removal -->
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#0f2a4a] mb-4">Can You Remove Stains from Car Upholstery?</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
          <strong>Yes, most car upholstery stains can be removed with professional extraction equipment and the right cleaning agents. We use oxygen-infused shampoos for fabric, pH-balanced cleaners for leather, and enzymatic treatments for organic stains like food and sweat. The sooner stains are treated, the higher the success rate.</strong>
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
          Common stains we remove include coffee, food spills, ink, sunscreen, sweat marks, and pet accidents. For fabric seats, hot water extraction pulls staining agents from deep within fibers. For leather, gentle agitation with a horse hair brush lifts stains without damaging the surface finish. We follow <a href="https://www.the-ida.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-[#0f2a4a] font-semibold hover:text-[#c0c7cf]">IDA</a> best practices for every material type.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Mobile vs Shop -->
